            release: { tr: "<strong>Web Push</strong> entegre, iki seçenek: (a) Firebase Cloud Messaging Web (<code>firebase/messaging</code>) ile FCM Web token alınıyor; (b) doğrudan <strong>VAPID key</strong> + <code>web-push</code> backend paketi ile native Web Push API. <strong>Service Worker</strong> push event'ini dinliyor. Test bildirimi tarayıcıya ulaşıyor. Subscription oluşturulurken backend'e <code>endpoint</code>, <code>keys.p256dh</code>, <code>keys.auth</code> ve user/device meta gönderiliyor. <strong>Token rotation</strong> handling 7.3'te detaylı (<code>pushsubscriptionchange</code>); bu maddenin sorumluluğu yalnızca ilk subscribe + backend kayıt akışı. <span class='hint'>iOS Safari için 16.4+ ve PWA standalone (Ana ekrana ekle) gerek.</span>", en: "<strong>Web Push</strong> is integrated, two options: (a) Firebase Cloud Messaging Web (<code>firebase/messaging</code>) with FCM Web token; (b) the native Web Push API directly with a <strong>VAPID key</strong> + <code>web-push</code> backend package. The <strong>Service Worker</strong> listens for push events. Test notifications reach the browser. On subscription, <code>endpoint</code>, <code>keys.p256dh</code>, <code>keys.auth</code> and user/device metadata are POSTed to the backend. <strong>Token rotation</strong> handling lives in 7.3 (<code>pushsubscriptionchange</code>); this item only covers the initial subscribe + backend persistence flow. <span class='hint'>iOS Safari requires 16.4+ and PWA standalone mode (Add to Home Screen).</span>" }
