            en: "1) An <strong>attestation layer</strong> in your backend: Firebase App Check (Play Integrity + App Attest + reCAPTCHA on web); for Appwrite & PocketBase your own hook + native attestation; for Amplify a Lambda authorizer + Play Integrity / App Attest verification; for Supabase verify the token inside an Edge Function; for Convex verify inside an action; for custom backend middleware before each endpoint. 2) Obtain an attestation token in the client: iOS <strong>DeviceCheck / App Attest</strong> API; Android <strong>Play Integrity API</strong>; web <strong>reCAPTCHA Enterprise</strong> or Cloudflare Turnstile. 3) Every sensitive request should carry this token in a header (e.g. <code>X-App-Attestation: ...</code>); reject (401/403) on the backend if it's missing/invalid. 4) Add a WAF layer (Cloudflare WAF / AWS WAF) to cut abnormal traffic early. 5) Review logs monthly; if fake-request rate is high, tighten the rules."
